# Implementation Plan: Subject Detail Page with Document Views & Preview Modal

This plan outlines the architecture and implementation steps to allow navigating into a Subject to view its uploaded documents in both Card and List formats, upload new documents, and preview files in a customized overlay modal.

## Proposed Changes

We will introduce a new page, three sub-components, and update routing and linking across the frontend.

---

### 1. Routing & Card Linking

#### [MODIFY] [App.jsx](file:///d:/megaProject/Sh-nm-i/Frontend/src/App.jsx)
- Register a new protected dynamic route: `/subjects/:subjectId` mapped to `SubjectDetail`.

#### [MODIFY] [SubjectCard.jsx](file:///d:/megaProject/Sh-nm-i/Frontend/src/components/subjects/SubjectCard.jsx)
- Import `useNavigate` from `react-router-dom`.
- Configure the outer container to navigate to `/subjects/${subject.subject_id}` when clicked.

---

### 2. New Reusable Document View Components

#### [NEW] [DocumentCardView.jsx](file:///d:/megaProject/Sh-nm-i/Frontend/src/components/subjects/DocumentCardView.jsx)
- Renders documents as grid cards with an icon (PDF vs Image vs Text), title, file size/date, processing status badges, and a delete button.
- Adds subtle hover effects aligned with the app's glassmorphism style.

#### [NEW] [DocumentListView.jsx](file:///d:/megaProject/Sh-nm-i/Frontend/src/components/subjects/DocumentListView.jsx)
- Renders documents in a compact, structured table list layout.
- Displays filename, upload date, status, preview trigger link, and delete action.

---

### 3. New Document Preview Component

#### [NEW] [DocumentPreviewModal.jsx](file:///d:/megaProject/Sh-nm-i/Frontend/src/components/subjects/DocumentPreviewModal.jsx)
- An overlay modal with backdrop blur to preview the file.
- If it's a PDF (`application/pdf`), embeds it using an `<iframe>` pointing to the secure Cloudinary URL.
- If it's an image (`image/*`), renders it via an `<img>` tag.
- Includes download link fallback and close action.

---

### 4. Detail Page Orchestration

#### [NEW] [SubjectDetail.jsx](file:///d:/megaProject/Sh-nm-i/Frontend/src/pages/SubjectDetail.jsx)
- Fetches all user subjects to find the name of the active subject (handles cases with 0 documents).
- Fetches all documents using `getUserDocuments()`, filtering for the current `subjectId`.
- Provides an inline document upload button using `uploadDocument(subjectId, file)`.
- Implements a polling loop (every 5 seconds) to update document statuses while any document is `'processing'`.
- Adds a visual switch/toggle at the top (`Card View` / `List View`).
- Renders `DocumentCardView` or `DocumentListView` based on the active selection.
- Manages the state to open/close `DocumentPreviewModal` when a document is clicked.

---

## Verification Plan

### Automated Build Verification
- Propose running `npm run build` in the `Frontend` workspace to check for code validation, TypeScript, and imports.

### Manual Verification
1. Navigate to the `/subjects` page.
2. Click on a subject card. Verify it opens `/subjects/:subjectId`.
3. Check the interface:
   - "Add Document" button: Clicking it prompts for a file upload, starts processing, and refreshes the view.
   - Toggle switch: Toggle between list layout and card layout and confirm responsiveness.
   - Document click: Confirm that clicking a completed PDF or image document pops up the preview modal, and it displays the content.
   - Close modal: Check that clicking overlay or close icon hides the preview modal.
